<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Theme Test Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/css/themes/apis.css">
    <script src="/static/js/theme-test.js"></script>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background-color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            color: #333;
        }
        .theme-info {
            background-color: #f5f5f5;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .theme-actions {
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        .btn {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            background-color: #007bff;
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin-right: 10px;
        }
        .file-content {
            background-color: #f8f9fa;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 4px;
            padding: 10px;
            font-family: monospace;
            white-space: pre-wrap;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Theme Test Page</h1>

        <div class="theme-info">
            <h2>Current Theme Information</h2>
            <p><strong>Theme Name:</strong> apis</p>
            <p><strong>CSS File:</strong> <span id="css-info">/static/css/themes/apis.css</span></p>
            <p><strong>Background Image:</strong> <span id="bg-info">Checking...</span></p>
        </div>

        <div class="theme-actions">
            <a href="/themetest/edit_css/apis" class="btn">Edit APIS Theme CSS</a>
            <a href="/themetest/help" class="btn">View Help</a>
        </div>

        <div class="debug-info">
            <h2>Debug Information</h2>
            <p>This page is a simple test to check if the theme system is working properly.</p>
            <p>If you can see this page with the honeycomb background, the theme system is working.</p>

            <h3>CSS File Content</h3>
            <div class="file-content">/* Theme: apis */
:root {
  --accent-color: #FFB900;
  --background-color: #FFF8E1;
  --border-color: #FFD54F;
  --footer-bg: #FFE082;
  --footer-text-color: #2C2C2C;
  --header-bg: #FFE082;
  --link-color: #B88A00;
  --link-hover-color: #805F00;
  --nav-bg: #FFE082;
  --nav-link-color: #2C2C2C;
  --nav-text: #2C2C2C;
  --primary-color: #FFF8E1;
  --secondary-color: #FFE8B8;
  --success-color: #27ae60;
  --table-header-bg: #FFE082;
  --text-color: #2C2C2C;
  --warning-color: #f39c12;
}

body {
  background-image: url('../images/BMaster/honey2.jpg');
  font-family: Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;
  font-size: 20px;
  color: black;
}</div>

            <h3>Troubleshooting</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Open your browser's developer tools (F12) to see if there are any errors</li>
                <li>Check if the CSS file is being loaded correctly</li>
                <li>Verify that the image path is correct</li>
                <li>Try clearing your browser cache (Ctrl+F5)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>